-- Manchester City Plans $95 Million Bid for Bale, News of the World Reports
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2010-12-05T12:54:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-05/manchester-city-plans-95-million-bid-for-bale-news-of-the-world-says.html
Manchester City is planning a 60
million-pound ($95 million) bid for Tottenham winger Gareth
Bale, the News of the World reported, without citing anyone.  City would offer 50 million pounds, and striker Emmanuel
Adebayor, which it values at 10 million pounds, the newspaper
said.  There is set to be a clear out of fringe players at City in
January, the News of the World said. Ireland goalkeeper Shay
Given, and England internationals Shaun Wright-Phillips, Joleon
Lescott and Wayne Bridge may leave, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  